00:13:46.420 --> 00:13:49.720
Any portfolio that has higher
expected rate of return

00:13:49.720 --> 00:13:52.690
for the same level of
risk, so the vertical line.

00:13:52.690 --> 00:13:56.620
Any portfolio that has less
risk for the same level

00:13:56.620 --> 00:14:01.030
of expected returns, So
the western direction.

00:14:01.030 --> 00:14:10.050
And anything in this segment,
that orthant, or quadrant,

00:14:10.050 --> 00:14:11.910
is strictly preferred.

00:14:11.910 --> 00:14:15.390
So in the case of
IBM, if you draw

00:14:15.390 --> 00:14:19.530
the vertical and the horizontal
and ask the question,

00:14:19.530 --> 00:14:21.330
does GM lie in that area?

00:14:21.330 --> 00:14:21.930
No.

00:14:21.930 --> 00:14:24.390
If you do GM, and you
draw the vertical and then

00:14:24.390 --> 00:14:26.280
the horizontal
and asked does IBM

00:14:26.280 --> 00:14:29.100
lie in that strictly
preferred quadrant?

00:14:29.100 --> 00:14:30.820
The answer is no.

00:14:30.820 --> 00:14:33.780
So the answer to your
question about IBM versus GM,

00:14:33.780 --> 00:14:36.300
no, there isn't any
strict relationship

00:14:36.300 --> 00:14:38.970
that would say one would
always dominate the other.

00:14:38.970 --> 00:14:43.080
But if GM were here,
then IBM is clearly

00:14:43.080 --> 00:14:45.850
contained in that
preferred quadrant.

00:14:45.850 --> 00:14:49.210
So then the answer to your
