00:17:13.240 --> 00:17:18.579
because it's 75% of the
risky, 25% of the riskless,

00:17:18.579 --> 00:17:22.270
so you're going to get
closer to the risky asset.

00:17:22.270 --> 00:17:23.470
OK, great.

00:17:23.470 --> 00:17:28.569
So we've now
demonstrated that what

00:17:28.569 --> 00:17:32.140
I can achieve as an
investor, just mixing

00:17:32.140 --> 00:17:35.110
portfolio p with
the risk-free rate,

00:17:35.110 --> 00:17:38.620
is anywhere along that line.

00:17:38.620 --> 00:17:43.730
Now this analysis applies
to any portfolio p.

00:17:43.730 --> 00:17:46.550
So for example, suppose
I wanted to ask you,

00:17:46.550 --> 00:17:48.200
what risk-reward
trade-offs could I

00:17:48.200 --> 00:17:54.527
