rate with General Motors?

00:17:54.527 --> 00:17:55.610
What would that look like?

00:18:02.810 --> 00:18:04.487
Yeah, Ken?

00:18:04.487 --> 00:18:07.455
AUDIENCE: The line from
T-Bills through GM.

00:18:07.455 --> 00:18:08.830
ANDREW LO: Exactly,
that's right.

00:18:08.830 --> 00:18:10.788
If I wanted to mix T-Bills
with General Motors,

00:18:10.788 --> 00:18:13.270
I get that straight line
right through that dot.

00:18:13.270 --> 00:18:16.930
If I wanted to mix T-Bills with
IBM, I'd go through that dot,

00:18:16.930 --> 00:18:17.530
with IBM.

00:18:17.530 --> 00:18:19.240
If I wanted to mix
T-Bills with Motorola,

00:18:19.240 --> 00:18:20.710
I'd go through Motorola.

00:18:20.710 --> 00:18:25.210
And if I wanted to mix
T-Bills with any portfolio

00:18:25.210 --> 00:18:28.870
on that frontier, on
that upper branch,

00:18:28.870 --> 00:18:31.900
it would just be a
line between T-Bills

00:18:31.900 --> 00:18:34.330
and that point on
the upper branch.

00:18:34.330 --> 00:18:36.080
Right?

00:18:36.080 --> 00:18:37.900
So question.

00:18:37.900 --> 00:18:40.920
If I were to give you the
choice of mixing T-Bills

00:18:40.920 --> 00:18:50.242
with only one portfolio,
just one, which would it be?

00:18:50.242 --> 00:18:51.200
Which would you prefer?

00:18:54.068 --> 00:18:55.525
[INAUDIBLE]?

00:18:55.525 --> 00:18:57.900
AUDIENCE: The one where the
